body.p:
A single check-box or multiple check-boxes are used to present and edit the value on an
      attribute or element. 
      oxy_checkbox. This type of form control supports the following properties:

.
          For the Check Box form control, its value has to be check;






;

;

;

values - specifies the values that are committed when
            the check-boxes are selected. In case these values are not specified in the CSS, they
            are collected from the associated XML Schema;

. To make the Check box form control inherit its font from its parent element, set the
            fontInherit property to true.

;

. In case this property is not specified, the values property is used
          as label;

;

.

example.codeblock:
checkBox[attribute]:before {
    content: "A check box editor that edits a two valued attribute (On/Off).
              The values are specified in the CSS:"
oxy_editor(
    type, check,
        edit, "@attribute",
        values, "On",
        uncheckedValues, "Off",
        labels, "On/Off"); 
}
